      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-hemolysis-vr-01",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD vs. measured hemolysis index — multi-site comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against hemolysis measurements collected across three perfusion laboratories operating the FDA generic centrifugal pump at five flow-speed operating points (2 L/min–3000 RPM through 6 L/min–2000 RPM). Mean absolute error across all operating points was 0.0031 g/100 L, well within the acceptance band. The data collection protocol involved routine clinical-equivalent perfusion runs at each site; sample timing and anticoagulation management followed each site's standard operating procedures rather than a pre-specified experimental protocol with randomised controls. CFD predictions fell within ±12% of measured NIH at all five operating points, and the relative hemolysis index RH remained below 1.0 for all configurations evaluated, satisfying the acceptance criterion.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-hemolysis-obs-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "name": "Multi-site perfusion laboratory hemolysis observation campaign",
        "description": "Hemolysis index measurements were obtained prospectively from three independent clinical perfusion laboratories. Each laboratory operated the FDA generic centrifugal pump at the five nominated operating points during routine pre-clinical device evaluation sessions. Blood samples were drawn from the circuit reservoir at steady-state and analysed by the plasma-free haemoglobin spectrophotometric method per ASTM F1841. No randomisation, blinding, or experimental manipulation of independent variables was performed; operating conditions were set to match the COU flow-speed matrix but were not otherwise controlled across sites.",
        "startedAtTime": "2024-06-01T08:00:00Z",
